CVE-2025-46653: Switch from hexoid to cuid2 for secure random ID generation

Formidable 2.x before 2.1.3 relies on hexoid to prevent guessing of filenames
for untrusted executable content; however, hexoid is documented as not
cryptographically secure. This patch replaces hexoid with @paralleldrive/cuid2
which provides cryptographically secure random ID generation.

Origin: upstream, https://github.com/node-formidable/formidable/commit/37a3e89fca1ed68ec674a539f13aafd62221ddaa

